    reviewSlug: 'content-scorecard',
  },
  {
    id: 'q4',
    question: 'Your Pulse survey returns NPS 22 and Memorable 5.2. What\'s the next step?',
    options: [
      'Ship it — 22 is a positive NPS',
      'Run the Full survey to diagnose which dimensions need work',
      'Send the Recall survey to check retention',
      'Revise the material immediately — this is a failing score',
    ],
    correctIndex: 1,
    explanation: 'NPS 22 is below the 30+ threshold for shipping. It\'s not a crisis (NPS is positive), but it needs diagnostics. Run the Full survey with all five semantic pairs to identify exactly which dimensions are dragging the score down.',
    reviewSlug: 'running-a-scorecard',
  },
  {
    id: 'q5',
    question: 'What does the Recall survey measure that Pulse and Full surveys do not?',
    options: [
      'Whether players enjoyed the material in the moment',
      'Which semantic pairs scored lowest',
      'Whether players remember key messages and changed behavior 7–14 days later',
      'How many players completed the survey',
    ],
    correctIndex: 2,
    explanation: 'The Recall survey goes out 7–14 days after exposure. It tests three things the other surveys can\'t: free recall (what do you remember?), knowledge retention (true/false checks), and behavioral follow-through (did you actually do anything differently?). Material that scores well on Pulse but fails on Recall is engaging but not memorable.',
    reviewSlug: 'running-a-scorecard',
